{"ts": "2026-05-04T21:17:04Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "add-parent-epic-alignment-check-to-refine-clarify-critic", "findings": ["The HIGH intent-clarity rating cites 'specific output shape (Apply/Dismiss/Ask)' but the source does not specify how the new (a)/(b)/(c) sub-questions integrate with the existing critic rubric — single-pass vs separate, shared finding budget, distinguishability in emitted output.", "The 'considerations for Research propagating into the clarified-intent → Research handoff' is cited as a concrete deliverable but the propagation mechanism is undefined — no documented 'considerations' channel exists in refine's handoff today.", "The Failure-mode-degradation enumeration describes what-to-do but not where-detection-lives or who emits the warning, and 'non-epic parent' detection is not defined (frontmatter field? naming convention?).", "Sibling-driven evolution / stale epics is declared out-of-scope but is actually an in-scope failure mode of the proposed check (false-positive Apply findings); source provides no specific pathway for stale-epic suspicion.", "Requirements alignment claims 'no conflicts' by citing 'Iterative improvement' and 'Maintainability through simplicity' but does not weigh the proposal's specific cost (added conditional branching in shared agentic skill) — cherry-picks confirmations.", "Criticality reasoning cites 'shared across lifecycle and overnight' but the source does not establish that overnight invokes clarify-critic; refine is the entry point and may be interactive-only.", "Complexity reasoning cites 'may extend clarify_critic event schema' but the source body never mentions event schema, events.log, or telemetry — assessor imported a likely-true implementation consequence as scope evidence.", "Sub-question (a) 'does the clarified intent align with the parent epic's intent?' is asked without operationalizing the alignment criterion (semantic overlap? deliverable subsumption? non-contradiction?); the central evaluative term is delegated to agent interpretation."], "dispositions": {"apply": 3, "dismiss": 5, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised requirements-alignment reasoning to acknowledge minor tension with 'Maintainability through simplicity' (added conditional branching in shared skill) while concluding alignment overall; MUST-escalation policy is not applicable (no MUST language added).", "Corrected criticality reasoning: refine is interactive (pre-overnight) and produces specs overnight executes; clarify-critic is upstream of overnight rather than invoked from it; criticality remains 'high' per 'shared skills that other capabilities depend on'.", "Removed 'may extend the clarify_critic event schema' from complexity reasoning since the source does not establish it; complexity remains 'complex' on multiple-files, shared-skill, conditional-behavior, and default-to-complex-on-skill-changes grounds."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "Rubric integration mechanics (single-pass vs separate, finding budget, output tagging) are Spec-phase decisions — the clarified intent of 'extend clarify-critic with parent-epic alignment rubric' is well-bounded for Clarify."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "The propagation channel for 'considerations for Research' (new dispatch-prompt field, addendum to clarified intent, separate file) is a Spec-phase implementation decision; the clarified intent of 'downstream Research dispatch is epic-aware in scope' is bounded."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "Detection-site (dispatcher vs critic) and the 'non-epic' predicate are Spec-phase decisions; the clarified intent of 'degrade gracefully across the four enumerated edge cases' is bounded."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Existing Apply/Dismiss/Ask framework already covers stale-epic / sibling-evolved cases — operator dispositions as Dismiss with rationale 'epic stale, sibling-evolved'. Source explicitly says Dismiss is for 'deliberate divergences justified in-place'. No new pathway needed."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Output structure is deterministic (Apply/Dismiss/Ask) and the existing clarify-critic already delegates evaluative judgment to agent reasoning — agent judgment is acceptable when output structure is bounded. Alignment criteria can be elaborated in Spec without changing the clarified intent."}], "status": "ok"}
